connect cities is a simple train game running in linux terminal. 
object of the game is to conect the cities, represented by the '@' character, using train tracks.  
building tracks cost money. 
once you connect two cities together, you can run a train between them, when a train goes form one city to another, you get money allowing you to build more tracks.

controls are displayed on screen in game.
-arrow keys move cursor
-'y' allows you to lay down track. press again to stop placing track. 
-'g' runs a train to all connected cities
-'q' quits



uses the ncurses library to handle display.
when compiling using gcc needs the -lncurses compiler flag.
